    <head>
        <title>‘recombit’</title>
        </head>
    <body>
        <!-- Not 'recombinant waybit'.  It would clash with the biological terminology.
          There 'recombinant' means formed by recombination, which is not the meaning here. -->


<section      id='recombit'>
    <h2><a href='#recombit'>
                  recombit</a></h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            each of two or more alternative inscriptions
            of a <a href='http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/script/waybit'>
            waybit</a> that arise by editing and are found at the same <a href='locus'>locus</a>
            <!-- After the definition of ‘allele’ in the Oxford dictionary of English, 2nd edition.
              Edited by Judy Pearsall, Patrick Hanks, Catherine Soanes and Angus Stevenson.
              Oxford University Press, Oxford, 2003. -->
            </li>
        <li>
            each of two or more <a href='co-local'>
            co-local</a>, <a href='clone'>
            non-clonal</a> waybits
            <ul>
                <li>
                    the <a href='http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/wayical'>
                    wayical</a> analogue of an allele, or ‘allelomorph’
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>


        </body>
    </html>
